{
    "name": "Monkey Swarm",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> warm forests<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary, pair, mission (3\u20136 swarms), or tribe (7\u201312 swarms plus 1\u20134 gorillas)<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Coordinated Swarm (Ex)</b> A monkey swarm coordinates its attacks more than a typical swarm, and deals swarm damage one step higher than a swarm of its HD would normally cause."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Monkeys sometimes travel in huge colonies of hundreds of individuals. In such quantities, these primates can become quite dangerous, capable of overwhelming many foes by their sheer numbers.<br/><br/>Unlike most swarms, monkey swarms work well together. A swarm of monkeys does not possess a true hive mind, but it is capable of working in tandem with other swarms to make basic tactical decisions in combat."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>Screeches and bestial calls precede this pack of monkeys, each primate propelling itself forward on calloused knuckles.</i>",
